stylometry: There are tradeoffs between production/ordering costs and holding costs. A manager must decide whether to incur the cost of producing or to hold off producing. This will be decided on whichever makes the business the most profits. Costs of producing will include all fixed costs, variable costs, and labor hours. Holding costs will include the amount of money spent to hold on the the product, such as warehouse expenses or the expense that may be incurred due to shelf-space/ loss of life in the product (meaning the product may lose its normal functions if stored and will not be used as it was produced for).
